(Practice: HTTP Performance & Persistence, DNS Resolution Mechanics, Network Performance Metrics) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Question 1) Tj
T*
(In the Domain Name System \(DNS\), a local DNS server is tasked with resolving a hostname) Tj
T*
(for which it has no cached records. If the local DNS server is configured to use) Tj
T*
(iterative queries, which of the following best describes the sequence of interactions) Tj
T*
(required to resolve the name?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Answer: D) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Solution:) Tj
T*
(In an iterative DNS query, the local DNS server manages the resolution process by) Tj
T*
(contacting different hierarchy levels itself. It first queries a Root server, which) Tj
T*
(provides a referral to the TLD server. It then queries the TLD server, which provides a) Tj
T*
(referral to the Authoritative server. Finally, it queries the Authoritative server to) Tj
T*
(obtain the specific IP address mapping. This is distinct from recursive queries where) Tj
T*
(the contacted server takes on the responsibility of returning the final mapping.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Question 2) Tj
T*
(Consider a scenario where a client uses HTTP/1.1 with persistent connections \(without) Tj
T*
(pipelining\) to retrieve a base HTML file and 6 embedded images from a server. The Round) Tj
T*
(Trip Time \(RTT\) between the client and the server is 50 ms. Assume the transmission time) Tj
T*
(for the request messages and the small objects is negligible. How much total time \(in) Tj
T*
(milliseconds\) elapses from the moment the client initiates the TCP connection until the) Tj
T*
(last image is fully received?) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Answer: 400 ms) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Solution:) Tj
T*
(In HTTP/1.1 persistent connections without pipelining, the process begins with a TCP) Tj
T*
(three-way handshake \(1 RTT\). The base HTML file is then requested and received \(1 RTT\).) Tj
T*
(Because the connection is persistent, the client does not need to re-establish the TCP) Tj
T*
(connection for the embedded objects. However, without pipelining, the client must send) Tj
T*
(each of the 6 image requests sequentially, waiting for the previous response to arrive) Tj
T*
(before sending the next, resulting in 6 additional RTTs. Total time = \(1 + 1 + 6\) * 50) Tj
T*
(ms = 400 ms.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Question 3) Tj
T*
(A point-to-point fiber optic link has a bandwidth of 10 Gbps and a length of 2,000 km.) Tj
T*
(The propagation speed of the signal in the fiber is 200,000 km/s. Calculate the) Tj
T*
(bandwidth-delay product for this link in bits. Additionally, determine the physical) Tj
T*
(length \(in meters\) of a single bit as it propagates through the fiber.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Answer: BDP: 100,000,000 bits; Bit Length: 0.02 meters) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Solution:) Tj
T*
ET
