(The Bandwidth-Delay Product \(BDP\) is calculated as Bandwidth \(R\) multiplied by) Tj
T*
(Propagation Delay \(d_prop\). Here, d_prop = 2,000 km / 200,000 km/s = 0.01 seconds. BDP =) Tj
T*
(10^10 bps * 0.01 s = 10^8 bits. The physical length of a bit is the distance the signal) Tj
T*
(travels during the time it takes to transmit one bit \(1/R\). Length = Speed \(v\) /) Tj
T*
(Bandwidth \(R\) = 200,000,000 m/s / 10,000,000,000 bps = 0.02 meters.) Tj
T*
